        <section id="overview" class="section">
            <h2>üìã System Overview</h2>
            <p>The A.R.I.A. (Advanced RLV Integration & Administration) Controller System is a comprehensive, modular RLV collar system for Second Life. Built with a focus on modularity, security, and user experience, it provides a complete platform for RLV interaction management.</p>
            
            <div class="feature-list">
                <div class="feature-item">
                    <h5>üèóÔ∏è Modular Architecture</h5>
                    <p>Clean separation of concerns with independent modules for each RLV functionality</p>
                </div>
                <div class="feature-item">
                    <h5>üîã Power Management</h5>
                    <p>Battery-based restriction system with automatic power management</p>
                </div>
                <div class="feature-item">
                    <h5>üé≠ Persona System</h5>
                    <p>Dynamic outfit and appearance management with RLV integration</p>
                </div>
                <div class="feature-item">
                    <h5>üì± Rich HUD Interface</h5>
                    <p>MOAP-based HTML displays with interactive controls and real-time status</p>
                </div>
                <div class="feature-item">
                    <h5>üîê Advanced Security</h5>
                    <p>Multi-tier permission system with configurable wearer admin mode</p>
                </div>
                <div class="feature-item">
                    <h5>üõ†Ô∏è Remote Management</h5>
                    <p>Programming station for advanced configuration and diagnostics</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="architecture" class="section">
            <h2>üèóÔ∏è System Architecture</h2>
            
            <h3>Core Components</h3>
            <div class="module-grid">
                <div class="module-card">
                    <h4>Main Module</h4>
                    <div class="version">v10.3</div>
                    <p><strong>Role:</strong> System kernel and coordination hub</p>
                    <p><strong>Functions:</strong> Module management, power control, user permissions, configuration broadcasting</p>
                    <span class="status-badge status-enhanced">Enhanced</span>
                </div>
                
