                    <h4>Permissions Module</h4>
                    <div class="version">v2.1</div>
                    <p><strong>Role:</strong> Access control and user management</p>
                    <p><strong>Functions:</strong> Admin/trusted user lists, wearer admin mode, permission validation</p>
                    <span class="status-badge status-enhanced">Enhanced</span>
                </div>
                
                <div class="module-card">
                    <h4>RLV Modules</h4>
                    <div class="version">v2.0+</div>
                    <p><strong>Role:</strong> Individual RLV functionality control</p>
                    <p><strong>Count:</strong> 8 specialized modules</p>
                    <span class="status-badge status-complete">Complete</span>
                </div>
                
                <div class="module-card">
                    <h4>HUD System</h4>
                    <div class="version">v2.2</div>
                    <p><strong>Role:</strong> Rich user interface with MOAP displays</p>
                    <p><strong>Functions:</strong> Status monitoring, module control, interactive HTML interface</p>
                    <span class="status-badge status-fixed">Fixed</span>
                </div>
            </div>

            <h3>Communication Protocol</h3>
            <p>All modules communicate via standardized linked messages with defined message codes:</p>
            <pre><code>// Core Communication Codes
integer UPDATE_BATTERY = 101;          // Battery level updates
integer UPDATE_CONFIG = 102;           // Configuration broadcasting  
integer MODULE_REGISTER = 200;         // Module registration
integer OPEN_MY_MENU = 201;           // Menu access requests
integer POWER_STATE_CHANGE = 300;     // Power on/off events
integer UPDATE_WEARER_ADMIN_MODE = 106; // Wearer admin mode toggle</code></pre>
        </section>

        <section id="modules" class="section">
            <h2>üì¶ RLV Modules</h2>
            <p>The A.R.I.A. system includes 8 specialized RLV modules, each handling specific functionality:</p>
            
            <div class="module-grid">
                <div class="module-card">
                    <h4>Speech RLV</h4>
                    <div class="version">v2.0</div>
                    <p>Controls communication restrictions including muting, gagging, and IM blocking with battery-aware automatic restrictions.</p>
                    <span class="status-badge status-complete">Complete</span>
                </div>
                
                <div class="module-card">
                    <h4>Mobility RLV</h4>
                    <div class="version">v2.0</div>
                    <p>Manages movement restrictions, location controls, teleport blocking, and sit/stand restrictions.</p>
                    <span class="status-badge status-complete">Complete</span>
                </div>
                
                <div class="module-card">
                    <h4>Vision RLV</h4>
                    <div class="version">v2.0</div>
                    <p>Handles sight restrictions including blindfolding, overlay management, and vision impairment effects.</p>
                    <span class="status-badge status-complete">Complete</span>
                </div>
                
                <div class="module-card">
                    <h4>Interface RLV</h4>
                    <div class="version">v2.0</div>
                    <p>Controls UI restrictions such as inventory access, world map, mini-map, and menu visibility.</p>
                    <span class="status-badge status-complete">Complete</span>
                </div>
                
                <div class="module-card">
                    <h4>Interaction RLV</h4>
                    <div class="version">v2.0</div>
                    <p>Manages touch restrictions, edit permissions, object rezzing, and world interaction controls.</p>
                    <span class="status-badge status-complete">Complete</span>
                </div>
                
                <div class="module-card">
                    <h4>Wardrobe RLV</h4>
                    <div class="version">v2.0</div>
                    <p>Advanced outfit and attachment management with conflict resolution and automatic wardrobe switching.</p>
                    <span class="status-badge status-complete">Complete</span>
                </div>
                
                <div class="module-card">
                    <h4>Tether RLV</h4>
                    <div class="version">v2.0</div>
                    <p>Following and leash functionality with target management, distance control, and visual leash effects.</p>
                    <span class="status-badge status-complete">Complete</span>
                </div>
                
                <div class="module-card">
                    <h4>Diagnostics RLV</h4>
                    <div class="version">v2.0</div>
                    <p>System diagnostics, RLV relay management, viewer queries, and system health monitoring.</p>
                    <span class="status-badge status-fixed">Fixed</span>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="installation" class="section">
            <h2>üöÄ Installation Guide</h2>
            
            <div class="warning">
                <h5>‚ö†Ô∏è Important Prerequisites</h5>
                <p>Before installation, ensure you have:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>RLV-enabled viewer (Firestorm recommended)</li>
                    <li>Basic LSL scripting knowledge</li>
                    <li>Ability to create and link prims</li>
                    <li>Understanding of Second Life permissions</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            
            <h3>Main Controller Installation</h3>
            <ol class="installation-steps">
                <li><strong>Create the Controller Object:</strong> Rez a prim and add additional child prims as needed for your design (minimum 4 prims recommended for HUD support).</li>
                <li><strong>Install Main Module:</strong> Copy the main_module.lsl script into the root prim.</li>
                <li><strong>Add Permissions Module:</strong> Copy the permissions_module.lsl script into any prim in the linkset.</li>
                <li><strong>Install RLV Modules:</strong> Add each of the 8 RLV module scripts to individual prims or distribute across the linkset.</li>
                <li><strong>Create Configuration:</strong> Add a notecard named "_config_aria.cfg" with your initial settings.</li>
                <li><strong>Test Basic Functions:</strong> Touch the object and verify the main menu appears.</li>
            </ol>
            
            <h3>HUD System Installation</h3>
            <ol class="installation-steps">
                <li><strong>Build HUD Object:</strong> Create a HUD-appropriate linkset with at least 4 prims for optimal display.</li>
                <li><strong>Install HUD Scripts:</strong> Add the three HUD scripts (main controller, app interface, status display) to appropriate prims.</li>
                <li><strong>Configure MOAP:</strong> Enable Media on a Prim for the display prims to allow HTML interfaces.</li>
                <li><strong>Attach and Test:</strong> Attach the HUD and verify it can scan for and connect to A.R.I.A. units.</li>
                <li><strong>Setup Permissions:</strong> Configure the HUD's communication channel and verify proper connectivity.</li>
            </ol>
            
            <div class="note">
                <h5>üí° Pro Tip</h5>
                <p>For best results, test the system in a sandbox environment before deploying to production. The modular design allows you to add modules gradually and test each component independently.</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="hud-system" class="section">
            <h2>üì± HUD System</h2>
            <p>The A.R.I.A. HUD provides a rich, interactive interface using MOAP (Media on a Prim) technology to display HTML-based controls and status information.</p>
            
            <h3>HUD Architecture</h3>
            <div class="module-grid">
                <div class="module-card">
                    <h4>Main Controller</h4>
                    <div class="version">v2.2.0</div>
                    <p>Primary HUD logic with HTML interface generation, A.R.I.A. unit scanning, and connection management.</p>
                    <span class="status-badge status-fixed">Fixed MAIN_PRIM Error</span>
                </div>
                
                <div class="module-card">
                    <h4>App Interface</h4>
                    <div class="version">v1.5</div>
                    <p>Module-specific interfaces for detailed control of individual RLV modules with rich HTML displays.</p>
                    <span class="status-badge status-complete">Complete</span>
                </div>
                
                <div class="module-card">
                    <h4>Status Display</h4>
                    <div class="version">v1.5</div>
                    <p>Real-time status monitoring with battery indicators, connection status, and system health displays.</p>
                    <span class="status-badge status-complete">Complete</span>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <h3>Key Features</h3>
            <div class="feature-list">
                <div class="feature-item">
                    <h5>üé® Rich HTML Interface</h5>
                    <p>Beautiful, responsive HTML displays with CSS styling and interactive buttons</p>
                </div>
                <div class="feature-item">
                    <h5>üîÑ Real-time Updates</h5>
                    <p>Live status monitoring with automatic refresh and visual notifications</p>
                </div>
                <div class="feature-item">
                    <h5>üì° Smart Scanning</h5>
                    <p>Automatic A.R.I.A. unit detection with range-based filtering</p>
                </div>
                <div class="feature-item">
                    <h5>‚ö° No Forced Attachment</h5>
                    <p>Works both attached and in-world with auto-detection of attachment state</p>
                </div>
                <div class="feature-item">
                    <h5>üîß Module Integration</h5>
                    <p>Seamless integration with all RLV modules for comprehensive control</p>
                </div>
                <div class="feature-item">
                    <h5>üîã Battery Monitoring</h5>
                    <p>Visual battery indicators with low-power warnings and charging status</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="warning">
                <h5>‚ö†Ô∏è MOAP Requirements</h5>
                <p>The rich HTML interface requires Media on a Prim (MOAP) to be enabled. Users may need to manually zoom and interact with the media surface for optimal display.</p>
            </div>
