        <section id="support" class="section">
            <h2>üõ†Ô∏è Support & Resources</h2>
            
            <h3>Getting Help</h3>
            <p>If you encounter issues or need assistance with the A.R.I.A. system:</p>
            
            <div class="feature-list">
                <div class="feature-item">
                    <h5>üìñ Documentation</h5>
                    <p>Comprehensive guides and API documentation available in this site</p>
                </div>
                <div class="feature-item">
                    <h5>üêõ Bug Reports</h5>
                    <p>Report issues via GitHub Issues with detailed error information</p>
                </div>
                <div class="feature-item">
                    <h5>üí¨ Community Support</h5>
                    <p>Join our Discord community for real-time help and discussions</p>
                </div>
                <div class="feature-item">
                    <h5>üìß Direct Contact</h5>
                    <p>Contact BrittRose-SL directly for complex technical issues</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <h3>Common Issues & Solutions</h3>
            
            <div class="note">
                <h5>üí° RLV Not Responding</h5>
                <p><strong>Solution:</strong> Ensure RLV is enabled in your viewer preferences. Check that the A.R.I.A. unit has proper permissions and the wearer has consented to RLV commands.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="note">
                <h5>üí° Modules Not Registering</h5>
                <p><strong>Solution:</strong> Verify all scripts are in the same linkset and that the main module is in the root prim. Check for script errors and reset if necessary.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="note">
                <h5>üí° HUD Display Issues</h5>
                <p><strong>Solution:</strong> Ensure MOAP is enabled for the HUD prims. Users may need to manually zoom and interact with the media surface. Check viewer media settings.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="note">
                <h5>üí° Configuration Not Loading</h5>
                <p><strong>Solution:</strong> Verify the "_config_aria.cfg" notecard exists and has proper formatting. Check for syntax errors in configuration entries.</p>
            </div>
            
            <h3>Technical Specifications</h3>
            <div class="module-grid">
                <div class="module-card">
                    <h4>System Requirements</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li>RLV-enabled viewer (1.23+ or Firestorm)</li>
                        <li>Minimum 4 prims for basic functionality</li>
                        <li>MOAP support for HUD displays</li>
                        <li>Script memory: ~2MB total for all modules</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                
                <div class="module-card">
                    <h4>Performance Metrics</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Script time: <0.5ms average per module</li>
                        <li>Memory usage: 15-25KB per script</li>
                        <li>Battery life: 2-24 hours depending on usage</li>
                        <li>Range: 20m default, 96m maximum for scanning</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                
                <div class="module-card">
                    <h4>Compatibility</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li>All RLV-enabled viewers supported</li>
                        <li>OpenCollar command compatibility layer</li>
                        <li>Standard LSL functions only</li>
                        <li>Cross-platform (Windows, Mac, Linux)</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                
                <div class="module-card">
                    <h4>Security Features</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Multi-tier permission system</li>
                        <li>Encrypted configuration storage</li>
                        <li>Automatic security timeouts</li>
                        <li>Safe word / SOS functionality</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

